<SLUG> BC-FBC-USCNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VANDERMADE SOLID IN FRESHMAN DEBUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC may have defeated Penn State convincingly, but
there's still suspense regarding a couple of starting positions as
the Trojans take a week off before next week's game against
Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   Freshman left guard Lenny Vandermade made an impressive debut,
and could push senior Trevor Roberts, who sat out the opener with a
sprained foot.
</P>
<P>
   ``Trevor will be in a fist fight to get that job back,'' USC
coach Paul Hackett said. ``We've got a battle going on there.''
</P>
<P>
   Roberts is questionable for the Colorado game, but expects to
play. Hackett said a player will not lose his job to injury but
added that Vandermade has a chance to be a four-year starter.
Vandermade is also the Trojans' back-up center.
</P>
<P>
   The other tight race is at cornerback, where Darrell Rideaux and
Chris Cash remain neck-and-neck for the starting spot.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's so close,'' Hackett said. ``Darrell was a little bit
ahead with experience, so he started the first game, but that could
go either way.''
</P>
<P>
   On punt returns, the Trojans will keep alternating Kareem Kelly
and Kris Richard but also begin working Frank Strong and Kevin
Arbet into the mix when Kelly and Richard need a break.
</P>
<P>
   Fighting mad: A remarkable streak came to an end Thursday, when
the Trojans had their first fights during a practice. Offensive
tackle Brent McCaffrey got into a scuffle with defensive end Sultan
Abdul-Malik, followed by another incident between tight end Doyal
Butler and linebacker Chris Prosser.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we want to play a game,'' Hackett said. ``If I had a
choice, we'd play a game and not have a bye.''
</P>
<P>
   Fumble control: While there have been nothing but accolades for
tailback Sultan McCullough's 128-yard performance against Penn
State, Hackett said he was ``concerned'' over a fumble in the
second half.
</P>
<P>
   ``He had one fumble and one ball that came out on the ground,''
Hackett said. ``I'm of the opinion it's a three-way battle (at
tailback) and is going to be until there is a clear-cut guy.
McCullough has an edge, no doubt about it.''
</P>
<P>
   McGuire returns: Offensive lineman Joe McGuire returned to
practice after missing a day with a strained back, an injury he
suffered in a summer all-star game. ``It's a little sore but I'm
OK,'' McGuire said.
</P>
<P>
   Play of the day: USC's reserves scrimmaged at the end of
practice, with the highlight an 80-yard touchdown pass from
quarterback Matt Cassel of Chatsworth High to wide receiver Sandy
Fletcher.
</P>
<P>
   Hospital visit: The Trojans will visit patients at several
hospitals today at the USC Health Sciences Campus, including the
USC Norris Comprehensive Cancer Center and Hospital, Women's and
Children's Hospital and USC University Hospital.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
