<SLUG> BC-ONE-A-DAY-MED-BRIEF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IS YOUR MALL HANDICAPPED-COMPLIANT?  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;    (This premium feature from The New York Times Syndicate is
available for a limited time without charge to clients of this news
wire.)
 &HT;    
 &HT;    
 By SAM URETSKY  
 c.2000 HealthScout.com  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by The New York Times Syndicate) &LR;  &QL;
<P>
   The Americans With Disabilities Act was passed in 1990 to ensure
that people with physical disabilities have reasonable access to
public places.
</P>
<P>
   The law mandates special parking spaces, wheelchair ramps and
doors that can be opened by a person in a wheelchair. While the law
was designed for people with disabilities, some of its provisions
have been beneficial for other groups, too. The curb cuts and wider
store aisles have been a boon to parents with baby carriages and
strollers.
</P>
<P>
   But how good is compliance? According to the May-June issue of
Public Health Nursing, it's been erratic.
</P>
<P>
   When researchers at the University of New Mexico examined local
shopping malls _ including those built after the law was passed _
they found a large number of violations. Some malls lacked proper
wheelchair ramps, while others had ramps that couldn't be used
because there were no curb cuts.
</P>
<P>
   There was only one item on which all malls scored 100 percent _
every mall surveyed had accessible pay phones.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT HEALTHSCOUT:
</P>
<P>
   HealthScout (http://www.healthscout.com) is a service of Rx
Remedy, Inc., a leader in the field of health information and
publisher of REMEDY Magazine, a prize-winning health publication
read in 2.2 American homes.
</P>
<P>
   -- All of HealthScout's original stories are based on primary
sources: reports in refereed medical journals and interviews with
the medical researchers who authored them. Fact-checkers
independently confirm reporters' work on sensitive stories.
</P>
<P>
   -- HealthScout's medical writers and editors have previously
worked at many of the nation's most respected newspapers and
magazines.
</P>
<P>
   -- HealthScout's Scientific Advisory Board includes leading
authorities in more than a dozen disciplines.
</P>
