<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards By Jimmy Chuang States News Service
Washington, September 1 -- Hahnemann University of Philadelphia won
a $100,000 contract from the Federal Prison Camp in Montgomery for
medical services.
</P>
<P>
   Earth Savers Inc. of Oakdale won a $67,400 contract from the
Department of Transportation in Cleveland for maintenance, repair
or alteration of real property.
</P>
<P>
   Midatlantic Construction and Design Associates of Yardley won a
$112,951 contract from the Department of Transportation in
Cleveland for fire damage repairs.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $68,546 contract from
the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for circuit card
assemblies.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $99,550 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for turbine
fastener rods.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $66,120 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for door
tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Triumph Controls Inc. of North Wales won a $86,744 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engine
control assemblies.
</P>
<P>
   Creative Precision East Inc. of Marcus Hook won a $123,213
contract from the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va.,
for aircraft components and accessories.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense L.P. of York won a $7 million contract from the
U.S. Army in Warren, Mich., for ground effect vehicles, motor
vehicles, trailers and cycles.
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
