   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ While some of the American educational reforms
were changed after Allied occupation forces left Japan in 1952,
most of the American-imposed reforms stayed in place and were
responsible for Japan's meteoric postwar rise to international
economic power. Now Japanese school children routinely wipe the
floor with American school children whenever or however scholastic
achievement is compared. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
