   BEETLEBAILEY-WALKER _ On Sept. 4, 1950, a college layabout named
Beetle debuted in a dozen newspapers. He was the star of the last
comic strip approved by legendary publisher William Randolph
Hearst. Six months later, however, the struggling strip had grown
to only 25 papers, and there was talk of cancellation. Then Beetle
Bailey joined the Army _ and hasn't left Camp Swampy in half a
century. (Palm Beach Post) WITH PHOTOS. EDs: EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY,
