has become a morass for Mort Walker's International Museum of
Cartoon Art. After a promising start when it opened in Boca Raton
four years ago, the museum ran into fund-raising problems and is
now ready to leave town if things don't get better, Walker said.
The museum has even identified a possible site for the collection
in midtown Manhattan. If the building can be sold for the right
