   WELCOME BACK, MOM AND POP
</P>
<P>
   MOM-AND-POP-STORES-HARVARD-BUSINESS-REVIEW _ Retailers have long
assumed that bigger is better: Megastores mean broader product
selection and lower operating costs. But by networking smaller
stores, retailers can replicate big-store advantages and offer
shoppers greater convenience. A report. 900 words. By Richard
Metters, Michael Ketzenberg and George Gillen.
