<HEADER>
A8317 &Cx1f; tab-z
u a BC-DARK-SECRET-OF-COSMOS     09-01 1415
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DARK-SECRET-OF-COSMOS-DISCOVER-$ADV29-ART-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE SEARCH FOR MISSING MATTER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use Tue., Aug. 29, 2000, or anytime thereafter.) 
 ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by DISCOVER NEWS SERVICE clients.
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, see end of text. 
 (Color art is included.) 
 By KAREN WRIGHT 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    
 &HT;    Like doubting disciples, certain astronomers spend much of their
time looking for proof of an unseen hand at work in the cosmos.
 &HT;    In 1933, a Swiss astronomer named Fritz Zwicky proposed that
some otherworldly presence holds the visible world together;
