preliminary report on the July Concorde crash. By Donald G. McNeil
Jr.
</P>
<P>
   TAIWAN-CHINA (Taipei) _ Taiwan's president said that there is no
consensus in Taiwan on unification with China and that it is time
to consider other options. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-IRAQ (Jerusalem) _ Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
seemed unconcerned Friday about a possible threat from Iraq despite
a report that the United States will put a Patriot antimissile
battery on alert for possible deployment to Israel. By Deborah
Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   LATIN-AMERICA-DRUGS (Brasilia, Brazil) _ Twelve Latin American
heads of state at a summit meeting on drugs and rebels in their
region were told by Colombia's president that U.S. involvement in
Colombia will not create problems for their countries. By Larry
Rohter.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-DRUGS (Mexico City) _ Two generals have been arrested and
charged with links to drug trafficking.
</P>
