<P>
   AUSTIN-TAXCASE _ WASHINGTON _ Whether Advanced Delivery and
Chemical Systems Nevada, In c., failed to distribute enough income
to its Austin owners could cost the company $2 million, U.S. Tax
Court records show. (Moskal).
</P>
<P>
   ATTN AUSTIN EDS
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location Atlanta, category Business, subcategory Justice
</P>
<P>
   GA-ECONOMY _ An exhaustive study by a Washington, D.C. think
tank shows that Georgia outpaced the nation in jobs and wage growth
during the 1990s. But the state's economic boom wasn't reflected in
most workers' paychecks. Georgia's median wage of $11.31 an hour is
56 cents lower than the nation. ``The economy in Georgia is
growing,'' said one of the authors of the Economic Policy
Institute's 450-page tome ``The State of Working America. ``But
it's not necessarily transferring to big gains for workers at the
middle or the bottom.'' One in seven Georgians lives in poverty and
nearly 30 percent of the jobs in Georgia pay less than the wages
needed to lift a family of four out of poverty. Other key findings:
Americans are paying a high price for prosperity.We're making more
money and wracking up loads of overtime and debt in the process.
(Joyner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH CHARTS.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-PILOTS _ The new pilot contract at United could cost
Atlanta-based Delta a bundle. That's because it appears to include
unusually hefty pay raises, which United was under pressure to pay
because of service woes. Delta pilots have been in talks for a year
and want an ``industry leading'' deal of their own, which means
they'll want to leapfrog the United deal. (Fonti, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
