<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CONCUSSIONS _ Concussions are common among high-school athletes.
Some 300,000 high-school athletes suffer concussions each year,
with a third of those injuries coming off the football field. What
is worrisome is that athletes sometimes don't tell anyone about
their injury. Successive concussions can lead to serious brain
damage, coma and even death, he said. (Chow, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   DIABETES COLUMN _ Traditionally an adult disease, it's growing
rapidly among the ranks of couch potato kids. (Lore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   SUMMER-FALL-MOVIES _ Dave Larsen's summer movie review and look
ahead to fall: ``At my signal, unleash hell.'' With those words,
Gladiator's Russell Crowe launched the 2000 summer movie
season.Crowe's command proved oddly prophetic for studios and
audiences alike. After Ridley Scott's thrilling historical epic,
which earned $181 million, summer's sizzle quickly fizzled.
(Larsen, Dayton Daily News). 33.
</P>
