President Clinton announces he will let his successor decide
whether to deploy a controversial missile-defense system that has
failed two tests. His statement immediately adds fuel to the raging
campaign debate over America's military might. Republican
presidential nominee George w. Bush charges that Clinton's decision
shows the administration is weak on defense. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
