</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-OUTLOOK (Washington) _ 1stLd-Writethru will be filed to
story that moved Thursday _ Congress returns this week for a final
month of work in which members will jockey to showcase an agenda
designed to win votes in November. Republicans are expected to push
tax cuts for small businesses and try to override presidential
vetoes on measures to repeal estate taxes and drop the so-called
marriage penalty. Democrats could win a boost in the minimum wage.
China is likely to receive permanent normal trade relations. By
JUDY HOLLAND. (1stld-writethru filed.)
</P>
