their convention in California ended in chaotic infighting, Pat
Buchanan and his rival for control of the Reform Party, John
Hagelin, have shifted their battle to Washington, D.C., where
federal campaign funds totally $12.6 million remain up for grabs.
By MARK HELM. (Filed Thursday.)
