   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Strikes make headlines, but what about
the really intimate workplace dynamics between managers and those
whom they supervise? Few topics are more interesting to us in our
own lives, but these topics are not well covered in the psychology
and political science courses we took in college, business school
curricula, or by the constant flow of inspirational business books.
The best way to get at them may be fiction. Who has written about
corporate competition better than John Le Carre? Or consider the
new novel ``Labor Day'' by Floyd Kemske. By David Warsh. 1100
words.
