</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-MISSILE (Washington) _ President Clinton says the United
States will continue researching national missile defense, but he
delays a decision on deployment until the next administration. By
John Donnelly. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GORE-DETAILS (Washington) _ On the campaign trail, Al Gore is
following his ``details'' strategy, an effort to contrast his
gravitas with George W. Bush's. By reeling off details _ many of
which voters aren't listening to or can't understand _ Gore is
betting that his wonky side will overcome Bush's charm. By Anne E.
Kornblut. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ARAB-PROFILING (Undated) _ A growing number of Muslims are
calling on the FAA to stop what they call airport profiling. The
FAA is preparing a $1.5 million study to determine if
Arab-Americans are being unfairly targeted in security checks. By
Cindy Rodriguez. 900 words. (a and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   MA-DRUG-USE (Boston) _ Blame it on the hippies. Or the liberals.
Or the college kids. Or the New Agers. Or the New York drug
dealers. The theories about why Massachusetts has such high drug
and alcohol use run the gamut. By Richard Saltus and Raja Mishra.
1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   HEMLOCK-MEETS (Boston) _ The controversial Hemlock Society is
co-sponsoring the World Assisted Dying Conference in Boston this
weekend, to the chagrin of groups representing Catholics and
disabled people. By Anne Barnard. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MARKETS-ECONOMY (Undated) _ Three economic reports boost Wall
Street hopes that the Federal Reserve might be done with its
inflation-fighting crusade. By Scott Bernard Nelson. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) _ Otis Smith was plucked off
the waiver wire by Bill Belichick for a purpose, that being Smith
knows his defensive system, understands how to be a role player and
what he adds in terms of leadership to the team might be his
largest attribute. By Nick Cafardo. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   MCDONOUGH-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Red Sox have had a lot of
things go wrong for them this year, but the worst could turn out to
be Jimy Williams' stuffing Izzy Alcantara in the closet for seven
weeks when he was with the team in July. By Will McDonough. 1800
words.
</P>
