<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service plans the following articles
from the Style section for use Sunday, Sept. 3, 2000, and
thereafter. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHOW-HOTSPOT (New York) _ Michael Chow, owner of the three
restaurants that bear his name, never intended to deliver diced
squab to the unremarkable. But for a good portion of the 1990s it
was largely the cachet-deficient who showed up, not only in New
York, but also in the Mr. Chows in Los Angeles and London. In the
past year or so, though, the Chow here has re-emerged as a
destination for all subspecies of the moneyed and glamorous, with
dumpling connoisseurs from the suburbs there, too. By Ginia
Bellefante.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   NITEOUT-AMANDA-PEET (New York) _ On the town with Amanda Peet,
star of the new movie, ``Whipped.'' By Linda Lee.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   ROBOT-DOGS (New York) _ After Sony's tail-wagging success with
its Aibo robo-dog _ it sold out its entire 45,000-unit production
run of the $2,500 electric critters last winter _ at least four toy
companies are putting their own, less expensive versions on the
market this fall. By Allen Salkin.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   FALL-FASHIONS-BOOKS (Undated) - When sorting through the guides
that tell you what is and is not stylish and important, it's
important to know who or what you aspire to, writes Penelope Green.
``Bright Young Things'' by Brooke de Ocampo, a contributing editor
at Vogue and ``card-carrying B.Y.T. herself,'' according to the
book's introduction, displays a huge menu of possibilities, and
possible settings.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Phyllostachys, or giant bamboo, can
form beautiful groves of canes _ culms, they are correctly called _
from 10 feet to more than 100 feet tall, depending on the species.
The culms are wonderfully varied in color: green, yellow, golden
orange; yellow with a vertical green stripe; green with a yellow
groove; mottled green and black, like snakeskin; as jet black as a
Steinway. By Anne Raver.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
