   CHINA-DOGMEAT _ DATONG, China _ In the 21st century, Zhang
Weilin believes China is moving beyond staples such as beef, pork
and chicken. People's palates are demanding dog meat, he says, but
the current market can't meet the demand. Rest assured, though,
where there's a perceived need in China, there's an entrepreneur
scheming to fill it. His company is raising St. Bernards to breed
with local mutts to produce a tasty dog that is the best of East
and West. And that's just the beginning of his plans to
revolutionize the dog meat industry. (Chao, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTOS.
