<P>
   MEDICAL-CARE _ Most Americans believe that they'll always have
access to medical care. But in fact, we all live in a state of
permanent medical instability. Almost anyone's personal coverage
could be changed or snatched away at any time. Here are the things
to watch out for. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CFO _ You can probably name baseball players that have stuck
with one team longer than the CFO of your favorite company has been
with that organization. Get used to it. Job-hopping has become a
career path for chief financial officers. So far this year, 43 of
Georgia's 244 publicly traded companies have replaced their chief
financial officers. With box on company officers' duties; small
graphic demonstrating the domino affect when a CFO leaves.
(McNaughton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
