<P>
   CONCUSSIONS _ Concussions are common among high-school athletes.
Some 300,000 high-school athletes suffer concussions each year,
with a third of those injuries coming off the football field. What
is worrisome is that athletes sometimes don't tell anyone about
their injury. Successive concussions can lead to serious brain
damage, coma and even death, he said. (Chow, Dayton Daily News)
