<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 19:07 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8782 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u f BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      09-01 0126
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following business
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Saturday, Sept. 2, and thereafter. For more information, contact
Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   THQ (Calabasas, Calif.) _ Video game maker THQ Inc. said Friday
that it has entered into a new line of credit with anumber of large
financial institutions, which will provide up to $50 million during
the firm's peak selling season. By Chris Sieroty.
</P>
<P>
   NOVACAP (Valencia, Calif.) _ NovaCap Inc., a subsidiary of Dover
Corp., has acquired Syfer Technology Ltd., a British manufacturer
of specialty ceramic electronic components. By Chris Sieroty.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
