<HEADLINE>
PLATTERS FOUNDER WINS COURT RULING 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (a and e coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RALPH RANALLI  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ A federal judge told singing group founder Herb Reed
Friday that ``only you'' have the rights to the Platters name.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. District Court Judge George O'Toole granted an injunction
keeping the fake Platters from joining The Drifters and Danny and
the Juniors on stage Friday night at the Festival of the Three
Saints in Lawrence.
</P>
<P>
   Reed, an Arlington resident, has fought for nearly six years for
the exclusive right to represent the group he helped found in 1953.
</P>
<P>
   Three years ago the First Circuit Court of Appeals affirmed his
