<P>
   CLOCKRADIO-GUNFIRE (Chatsworth, Calif.) _ John Dickson woke up
as usual to his clock radio, but then the fusillade of gunfire
erupted through his bedroom wall, sending him tumbling from bed. It
was his neighbor, upset about the clock as part of a long-standing
dispute, police said. The neighbor then barricaded himself in his
apartment, but surrendered peacefully later after tear gas was
used. By Dana Bartholomew. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
