public warning that their review of Firestone's data has found that
1.4 million Firestone tires, mainly sold to consumers as
replacements for factory-issued tires on sport utility vehicles and
pickup trucks, are even more prone to failure than tires recently
recalled on Ford Explorers and other Ford models. By Keith
Bradsher. (Scheduled to move by 8:45 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   EDS: TIRE-WARNING, an early, undated story by Julian E. Barnes
has moved.
</P>
<P>
   CHENEY-STOCKS (Undated) _ Dick Cheney says he is ``fully
prepared to forfeit'' oil-company stock options that he would
otherwise continue to hold after taking office if he and George W.
Bush win in November. The vice presidential nominee made the
statement as he prepared to release his financial disclosure forms
and 10 years of income tax returns. By Adam Clymer. (Scheduled to
