Taiwan's new president, Chen Shui-bian, has labored to convince
China that he is not a wild-eyed separatist, driven by dreams of
Taiwanese independence. But Chen's charm offensive has come to an
abrupt end. In an interview here, he took a harder line toward the
Chinese government on the crucial issue of when _ or even whether _
Taiwan and China will be unified. By Mark Landler. (The story has
moved in ``i'' news file.) 800 words.
</P>
