<HEADER>
A8879 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s BC-FBC-CAPSULES-NYT &LR;      09-01 0678
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-CAPSULES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KEY COLLEGE FOOTBALL GAMES 
</HEADLINE>
   By FRANK LITSKY   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   KEY GAMES
</P>
<P>
   No. 3 Alabama (0-0) at UCLA (0-0)
</P>
<P>
   Alabama, the Southeastern Conference's Western Division
favorite, has talent to burn. Freddie Milons, its flanker/running
back/trick-play quarterback, and Shaun Bohanon, its new tailback,
will test UCLA's improved defense. Alabama is favored, but UCLA
could be tough.
</P>
<P>
   No. 22 Southern Mississippi (0-0) at No. 13 Tennessee (0-0)
</P>
<P>
   With sophomore Joey Mathews succeeding Tee Martin at
quarterback, Tennessee is a division favorite in the Southeastern
Conference. If Southern Mississippi survives openers at Tennessee
and Alabama, it will be a national power.
</P>
