<P>
   HOWARD-BUFFETT-PROFILE (Decatur, Ill.) _ As the eldest son of
the so-called ``Oracle of Omaha,'' a man many consider the greatest
stock picker of all time, Howard Buffett is now positioned to
become the next chairman of Berkshire Hathaway, the holding company
his father turned into an investor's gold mine. A profile of the
younger Buffett, an investor in his own right. By David Barboza.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-BUSINESS (Undated) _ Despite scandal and huge expense,
Olympic sponsorships remain hugely popular, with revenues from them
setting new records this year. No matter what happens on the track,
in the pool or over the field, there may be no more dramatic an
Olympic comeback in 2000 than the one the IOC has pulled on the
sponsorship front. By Randall Lane.
</P>
<P>
   With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   DEBITCARDS-STUDENTS (Undated) _ Parents who hope to keep their
college-age kids from getting over their heads in debt often
arrange for them to have debit cards rather than credit cards for
emergencies. Card issuers are sabotaging that strategy by giving
debit-card kids ``overdraft protection'' that amounts to an
expensive revolving line of credit _ in other words, a credit card.
By Nancy Lloyd.
</P>
<P>
   With:
</P>
<P>
   DEBITCARD-DRAWBACKS (Undated) _ Little-known reasons debit cards
are a rotten deal for all consumers, and especially for financial
novices like college kids. By Nancy Lloyd.
