<P>
   FIVE-QUESTIONS-BANKRUPTCY (Undated) _ A decade ago, a trio of
scholars, in an award-winning analysis of bankruptcy filings,
destroyed the myth that most of those seeking refuge from creditors
were blue collar workers. People in every occupation go bankrupt in
rough proportion to their numbers, Elizabeth Warren, Teresa
Sullivan and Jay Lawrence Westbrook found in a widely praised study
of Bankruptcy Court records. Now they have refined their research
and shown that misfortune, not profligate living, is behind most
bankruptcy filings. By David Cay Johnston.
</P>
<P>
   MEA-CULPA-ADS (Undated) _ For chiefs in crisis, it's survival of
the sorriest. By Julie Flaherty.
