<P>
   INVEST-BROKERAGE (Undated) _ Brokers, according to Wall Street
truism, prosper when the market goes up and when it goes down. But
this year the market has gone nowhere _ no major average has moved
as much as 4 percent from its Dec. 31 level _ and the brokers have
done better than ever. And many in Wall Street think that brokerage
shares, despite rich prices and a history of sharp cyclical swings,
have still more room to fly. A major reason, analysts say, is how
they are taking business from banks in a new regulatory landscape
for which the banks themselves lobbied vigorously for decades. By
Robert D. Hershey Jr.
</P>
