<P>
   CHOW-HOTSPOT (New York) _ Michael Chow, owner of the three
restaurants that bear his name, never intended to deliver diced
squab to the unremarkable. But for a good portion of the 1990s it
was largely the cachet-deficient who showed up, not only in New
York, but also in the Mr. Chows in Los Angeles and London. In the
past year or so, though, the Chow here has re-emerged as a
destination for all subspecies of the moneyed and glamorous, with
dumpling connoisseurs from the suburbs there, too. By Ginia
Bellefante.
