<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Phyllostachys, or giant bamboo, can
form beautiful groves of canes _ culms, they are correctly called _
from 10 feet to more than 100 feet tall, depending on the species.
The culms are wonderfully varied in color: green, yellow, golden
orange; yellow with a vertical green stripe; green with a yellow
groove; mottled green and black, like snakeskin; as jet black as a
Steinway. By Anne Raver.
</P>
