<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, SEPT. 2 
</HEADLINE>
 (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-HAMAS-LEADER-NYT (moved Saturday, August 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, August
26 about Sheik Ahmed Yassin, spiritual leader of the Hamas
movement, misidentified the authority holding Mohammed Dief, a
Hamas member arrested on terrorism charges. It is the Palestinian
Authority; he is not in an Israeli jail.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PHILIPPINES-KIDNAP-NYT (moved Wednesday, August 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, August
30 about the kidnapping of an American by rebels in the Philippines
misstated a comment from a State Department spokesman about the
possibility of release negotiations. As the article noted, he said
the United States would not ``pay ransom, change policies, release
prisoners or make any concessions that reward hostage taking.'' He
did not rule out negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-WATKINS (moved Thursday, August 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Thursday, August
31 about John C.A. Watkins, a former publisher of The Providence
Journal, referred incorrectly to a survivor. Fanchon M. Burnham is
his daughter, not his son.
</P>
</TEXT>
