<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    EDS: Embargoed for Sunday, Sept. 3.
 &HT;    Panel unites TV, PC on 1 screen
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ If you can't decide whether you want to watch
television or work on your computer, Samsung offers a pair of
thin-profile monitors that lets you do both things at once.
</P>
<P>
   SyncMaster MP flat-panel monitors are liquid crystal monitors
for your computer but they also have built-in television tuners and
input jacks to accept programming from VCRs, camcorders, DVD
players and other devices.
</P>
<P>
   Using the monitors' picture-in-picture feature, users can
reserve a corner of the monitor screen to watch Olympic broadcasts
or recorded movies while using the rest of the screen to run
spreadsheet programs or surf the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   The monitors come in two sizes: the 15-inch SyncMaster 150MP
with a manufacturer's suggested price of $1,119, and the 17-inch
SyncMaster 170MP, which sells for about $1,769.
</P>
<P>
   Samsung spokesman Michael Ingalls said the monitors have
built-in stereo speakers and can be used as stand-alone television
sets. They can be connected to cable or satellite television
services or they can be used with an antenna to pick up local
broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
   The video screen has a digital zoom feature that allows viewers
to magnify images on the screen up to 64 times their normal size.
</P>
<P>
   Samsung is shipping the monitors to retail outlets, but they
aren't available yet in Dayton stores.
</P>
<P>
   For more information about the products, call Samsung at (800)
726-7864 (SAMSUNG) or visit the Web site at www.samsungmonitor.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
