<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOMICIDE-BAGELSHOP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAN RUN OVER, KILLED; DRIVER THEN BUYS BAGELS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JORDAN SMITH 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   VAN NUYS, Calif. _ A 65-year-old man was killed Friday in this
North Los Angeles community when a motorist hit him, backed over
him and then made a racial slur moments later while ordering
bagels, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The driver, Marie E. West of Hermosa Beach, hit Jesus Plascencia
as he walked out of the Western Bagel shop on Sepulveda Boulevard
just after 4 a.m., said Los Angeles Police Department Detective Al
Aldaz. Plascencia picked up bagels every morning for the nearby
delicatessen where he worked.
</P>
<P>
   West then put her car in reverse and hit Plascencia again -
dragging his body 30 feet north up Sepulveda - before returning to
the store to order bagels, Aldaz said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said while she was inside the store, West made
disparaging remarks about Latinos. A Western Bagel employee said
the woman commented, ``God, I hate Latinos.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We are handling this as hate-related,'' Aldaz said.
``Witnesses disclosed that the suspect intentionally hit him
repeatedly.''
</P>
<P>
   West was arrested on suspicion of murder, police said. The
attack was witnessed by 15 people, investigators said.
</P>
<P>
   West's husband, Al Bowman, said in an interview his wife is not
a racist. He said she has a history of mental illness, and that the
incident was the result of her ceasing to take medications.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's not a racist or anything - I'm half Mexican, and I can
tell you, she doesn't hate Mexicans,'' he said. ``If she'd hit a
Jew, she would've said she hates Jews, if she'd hit a black she
would've said she hates blacks.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This is part of her illness; if it were easy to figure out it
wouldn't be called mental illness.''
</P>
<P>
   Bowman said West has been hospitalized for bipolar disorder 18
times in the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
   Hermosa Beach police Watch Cmdr. John Koebsell said Bowman
called Thursday night to report that West was threatening to kill
him at their 7th Street home.
</P>
<P>
   ``By the time we arrived, she was already gone,'' he said. LAPD
spokesmen and detectives declined to comment about West's mental
state.
</P>
<P>
   Four bags of bagels littered the scene of the incident Friday
morning, just north of Stagg Street on Sepulveda Boulevard in Van
Nuys.
</P>
<P>
   Employees of the Western Bagel said Plascencia was a kind man
who came to the store every morning to buy bagels on his way to
work.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was a gentle man who didn't have a mean bone in his body,''
said one employee who asked not to be named. ``He was well-liked by
everybody, and I mean everybody. He was just at the wrong place at
the wrong time.''
</P>
<P>
   Plascencia had worked as a busboy for the past 14 years at
Weiler's Deli in North Hills. Manager Julie Shipley said he was
known for his smile.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was just a thin and frail man, but he was one of the best
busboys we ever had. All he ever did was smile,'' she said. ``He
picked up the bagels for us every day on the way to work - he
offered to do it. This was something he did every day, every year
for the past 14 years.''
</P>
<P>
   Shipley said the deli will be keeping a photo of Plascencia on
the counter as a memorial.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles County Deputy District Attorney Jacquelyn Lacey of
the department's hate crimes division said she expects to file
charges against West on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
